WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:04.036
<i>Previously on</i> reign:
How did we die, mother?

00:04.038 --> 00:07.006
Henriette: <i>Do to claude</i>
<i>what she did to us.</i>

00:07.008 --> 00:08.774
Claude's a healthy
young woman. It'll take

00:08.776 --> 00:10.676
<i>A lot more poison</i>
<i>to bring her down.</i>

00:10.678 --> 00:12.544
This is what you've been
putting in my soup, isn't it?

00:12.546 --> 00:14.780
Why?
You murdered
your sisters.

00:14.782 --> 00:17.249
Do not betray
your other children.

00:17.251 --> 00:20.319
I realize I can't change
the fact that...

00:20.321 --> 00:22.021
You blame me for
what happened.

00:22.023 --> 00:24.223
I believe that we should
lead separate lives.

00:24.225 --> 00:26.792
The money I gave you was never
going to build a school.

00:26.794 --> 00:30.529
Tell me we didn't fund an
assassination on our king.

00:30.531 --> 00:32.698
There are plans to
have bash legitimized.

00:32.700 --> 00:35.167
You're talking about changing
the line of succession,

00:35.169 --> 00:36.568
And that's
the sort of talk

00:36.570 --> 00:39.238
That gets bastards
and mistresses beheaded.

00:39.240 --> 00:41.106
Give this to queen mary,
but not until tomorrow.

00:41.108 --> 00:43.509
I know I agreed to marry claude
<i>of behalf of France,</i>

00:43.511 --> 00:45.044
<i>But I've realized I can't--</i>

00:45.046 --> 00:46.578
<i>I've fallen in love</i>
<i>with a queen.</i>

00:50.750 --> 00:52.651
Francis:
Mary.

00:54.087 --> 00:55.754
I was wondering
where you were

00:55.756 --> 00:58.123
When you didn't come
for breakfast.

00:58.125 --> 01:00.225
I was weary from my trip.
I've been in my chambers.

01:00.227 --> 01:01.660
Not avoiding me?

01:01.662 --> 01:03.495
It's been two days.

01:03.497 --> 01:05.130
I know that
you want distance,

01:05.132 --> 01:06.799
But we are king
and queen.

01:06.801 --> 01:09.535
I saw you-- the
night I returned.

01:09.537 --> 01:12.171
You were sleeping with lola.

01:12.173 --> 01:14.106
The two of you and your baby.

01:16.076 --> 01:18.077
Well, the baby refused
to sleep for days.

01:18.079 --> 01:19.211
Lola and I were
just exhausted.

01:19.213 --> 01:20.846
There's no need to explain.

01:20.848 --> 01:23.115
I know that there is nothing
untoward going on between you.

01:24.617 --> 01:26.118
But it still hurt

01:26.120 --> 01:28.654
To see you at
peace with them.

01:28.656 --> 01:30.689
Gave me a glimpse of
the happier life you could have.

01:30.691 --> 01:32.424
I want a happier life
with you.

01:34.828 --> 01:36.862
I'm sorry.

01:37.831 --> 01:39.231
It's not you.

01:39.233 --> 01:41.300
If any man comes close,
I-I get uneasy.

01:41.302 --> 01:43.502
I still can't bear
to be touched.

01:43.504 --> 01:45.337
Even the sound of a man
breathing near me...

01:45.339 --> 01:47.706
I wish I knew
how to help.
Just give me time.

01:47.708 --> 01:49.741
All the time you need,
of course.

01:52.812 --> 01:55.180
And how can I help you?

01:55.182 --> 01:57.382
I hear that you've been
parceling out narcisse's land.

01:57.384 --> 01:58.684
That can't be easy.

01:58.686 --> 02:01.220
It's a feeding frenzy,
truth be told.

02:01.222 --> 02:02.888
Impartial advice
is difficult

02:02.890 --> 02:05.791
When every counselor wants
a piece of the prize himself.

02:05.793 --> 02:08.327
I have more lands than
I could ever need.

02:09.429 --> 02:10.562
Perhaps I could help.

02:10.564 --> 02:12.131
I'd love that.

02:12.133 --> 02:13.732
And as you said,

02:13.734 --> 02:16.535
We may be apart, but our
duties still remain.

02:19.906 --> 02:22.641
What took you from our bed
so early this morning?

02:22.643 --> 02:24.209
Francis sent for me.

02:24.211 --> 02:25.611
Ah, did he want you to do

02:25.613 --> 02:27.412
His dark bidding again,
or was it simply

02:27.414 --> 02:29.181
A mÃ©nage Ã  trois
with your sister claude?

02:29.183 --> 02:31.617
Well, he wanted to offer me
lands and a title,

02:31.619 --> 02:33.819
But I said, "my wife wants
a husband with honor,

02:33.821 --> 02:35.254
So I must decline."

02:35.256 --> 02:36.922
That's not funny.

02:36.924 --> 02:38.924
Perhaps not, but it's true.

02:38.926 --> 02:41.460
The lands and
title part anyway.

02:41.462 --> 02:42.661
I wasn't stupid
enough to refuse.

02:42.663 --> 02:43.929
Wait, you're serious?

02:45.198 --> 02:47.299
Really? Oh, bash!

02:47.301 --> 02:48.767
And all this time,
I've been bowing

02:48.769 --> 02:50.502
And scraping
to countesses and barons,

02:50.504 --> 02:53.238
And now you're saying
they can bow to me?

02:53.240 --> 02:54.706
Who will bowing to me,
by the way?

02:54.708 --> 02:56.208
Countesses?
Do we get a duchy?

02:56.210 --> 02:58.177
Are you even aware
you're undressing me?

02:58.179 --> 02:59.611
(babbles)
uh, kenna, uh,
there's other news.

02:59.613 --> 03:01.346
Diane: I'm beginning
to understand

03:01.348 --> 03:03.282
What henry saw in her.

03:03.284 --> 03:05.350
Mother, you're early.

03:05.352 --> 03:07.753
Well, since you're here,
I suppose, uh,

03:07.755 --> 03:10.222
I should formally
present my new wife.

03:10.224 --> 03:12.925
So sorry I missed
the wedding.

03:12.927 --> 03:15.260
I heard you wept through
the entire thing.

03:15.262 --> 03:17.296
Better now?

03:17.298 --> 03:20.299
Uh, kenna, this is the news
I was trying to tell you about.

03:20.301 --> 03:24.369
Diane, to what do we owe
this unexpected pleasure?

03:24.371 --> 03:26.205
Are you here
for the ice festival?

03:26.207 --> 03:27.372
Bash hasn't told you?

03:27.374 --> 03:29.308
My son has gifted me

03:29.310 --> 03:31.877
Some of the lands granted
to him by francis.

03:31.879 --> 03:34.646
And, as I was staying
nearby with friends,

03:34.648 --> 03:36.281
He invited me here

03:36.283 --> 03:38.951
To go over the details
of my new estate.

03:38.953 --> 03:40.953
Well, that's lovely.

03:40.955 --> 03:42.588
Bash, darling,

03:42.590 --> 03:46.458
Did your mother's estate come
with a title perchance?

03:46.460 --> 03:48.894
Oh, bash doesn't care
about titles.

03:48.896 --> 03:50.963
Or he wouldn't have
turned down the duchy

03:50.965 --> 03:51.964
The king offered.

03:51.966 --> 03:52.998
Instead, he took

03:53.000 --> 03:54.433
The barony closer to francis

03:54.435 --> 03:56.268
So he could
continue to serve

03:56.270 --> 03:57.569
As the king's deputy.

03:57.571 --> 03:59.938
I could have been
a duchess.

03:59.940 --> 04:02.307
Have I caused marital discord?

04:03.576 --> 04:05.377
Nothing could be further
from my mind.

04:13.386 --> 04:15.387
Makeup, jewelry.

04:15.389 --> 04:17.389
They're all just
distractions

04:17.391 --> 04:19.291
To hide the corrupt
flesh underneath.

04:19.293 --> 04:21.293
Your flesh is not nearly
corrupt enough

04:21.295 --> 04:24.296
Since you started this
campaign of self-flagellation.

04:24.298 --> 04:26.698
And not the enjoyable kind.

04:26.700 --> 04:29.268
I've made a mess of this family.

04:29.270 --> 04:31.036
If only I knew how
to make things right.

04:31.038 --> 04:33.438
Run and play while I
talk to your father.

04:34.374 --> 04:36.708
And try not to scare
anyone to death.

04:36.710 --> 04:37.943
Especially claude.

04:39.912 --> 04:41.546
When I chose
to let claude live,

04:41.548 --> 04:42.881
I thought they'd
never forgive me.

04:42.883 --> 04:44.283
But they're not angry anymore.

04:44.285 --> 04:45.450
How did you do it?

04:45.452 --> 04:46.852
I listened, catherine.

04:46.854 --> 04:48.320
I gave them time,

04:48.322 --> 04:50.289
Respect and love.

04:50.291 --> 04:53.292
That's what families ought to
offer each other, isn't it?

04:53.294 --> 04:55.594
In a perfect world, yes.

04:55.596 --> 04:57.729
Not a perfect
world, catherine.

04:57.731 --> 05:01.800
This world, which is
so close to yours,

05:01.802 --> 05:04.336
If only you'd choose to
be more a part of it.

05:04.338 --> 05:06.638
How can I choose
to be a part of your world?

05:06.640 --> 05:08.940
I don't even know
if it's real, if you're real.

05:08.942 --> 05:10.075
Am I going mad?

05:10.077 --> 05:12.411
What does "real"
even mean, hmm?

05:14.380 --> 05:15.814
Hello, brother.

05:15.816 --> 05:17.816
You don't seem in
very high spirits.

05:17.818 --> 05:20.085
Wife troubles?

05:20.087 --> 05:21.687
If so, I'm sorry.

05:21.689 --> 05:23.322
I mean it, bash.

05:23.324 --> 05:24.623
Kenna was rather kind
to me, after all.

05:24.625 --> 05:25.991
What are you after?

05:25.993 --> 05:27.626
Do I have to be
after something

05:27.628 --> 05:29.961
If, for one moment,
I'm not being beastly?

05:29.963 --> 05:31.630
Is that really what
people think of me?

05:31.632 --> 05:32.864
Only the ones
who know you.

05:32.866 --> 05:35.867
I suppose it's
no wonder, then.

05:35.869 --> 05:40.339
The leap between beast and
murderer isn't so great, is it?

05:40.341 --> 05:42.541
My mother thinks I
killed the twins.

05:42.543 --> 05:44.476
To the point that she
was trying to poison me.

05:44.478 --> 05:46.345
Kenna was right.

05:46.347 --> 05:47.713
I was five.

05:47.715 --> 05:49.348
Can you imagine
what that's like?

05:49.350 --> 05:50.549
Being accused
of something

05:50.551 --> 05:52.484
You're too young
to even remember.

05:52.486 --> 05:54.052
This new post
you've taken,

05:54.054 --> 05:56.521
You get to the bottom
of things, don't you?

05:56.523 --> 05:58.357
You help people.

05:58.359 --> 06:00.559
You want me to look into it.

06:00.561 --> 06:02.361
That's what you're
after, isn't it?

06:07.633 --> 06:09.601
Tell me everything
you know.

06:09.603 --> 06:13.438
I suggest retaining
the montagnol chateau

06:13.440 --> 06:15.907
With the northwest parcels.

06:15.909 --> 06:17.976
They contain grain fields,
while the eastern lands

06:17.978 --> 06:19.511
Are suitable
for sheep husbandry.

06:19.513 --> 06:20.946
Good.

06:20.948 --> 06:22.948
List montagnol
and the northwest parcels

06:22.950 --> 06:24.082
As one holding.

06:24.084 --> 06:26.485
Mary:
Lord narcisse.

06:26.487 --> 06:30.389
So good to see you cooperating
in carving up your empire.

06:30.391 --> 06:32.791
What crime did you
confess to in the end?

06:32.793 --> 06:37.696
I'm guilty of embezzling
from the crown, majesty.

06:37.698 --> 06:39.398
Ah, embezzlement.

06:39.400 --> 06:41.500
Excellent choice.

06:41.502 --> 06:43.835
If you had been guilty
of blackmailing us--

06:43.837 --> 06:45.670
Unthinkable, really--

06:45.672 --> 06:48.507
We would have taken your
lands and your head.

06:48.509 --> 06:51.443
I am grateful
for the king's mercy.

06:51.445 --> 06:54.045
I only hope that
I can be useful.

06:54.047 --> 06:57.048
Francis, since it's time for the
king to take trusted counsel,

06:57.050 --> 07:00.519
I think lord narcisse would be
more useful outside the door.

07:00.521 --> 07:03.588
Thank you for your help,
narcisse. You may go.

07:09.629 --> 07:11.696
I assume the best parcels
of land are to go

07:11.698 --> 07:13.131
To narcisse's allies?

07:13.133 --> 07:15.500
He may bow and scrape
to save his neck,

07:15.502 --> 07:17.469
But they won't, not
unless we buy them off.

07:17.471 --> 07:19.471
Of course.

07:19.473 --> 07:22.073
But there still is a great deal
of land to give away.

07:22.075 --> 07:24.443
I want to start
by restoring some lands

07:24.445 --> 07:26.578
To the protestants
that narcisse stole them from.

07:26.580 --> 07:28.713
As long as you take care
to send the right message

07:28.715 --> 07:30.148
So soon after the castle attack.

07:30.150 --> 07:32.584
That's why I plan
to only give lands to lords

07:32.586 --> 07:33.718
Who have proven
their loyalty.

07:33.720 --> 07:35.520
Like lord condÃ©, you mean?

07:35.522 --> 07:37.989
Few protestants have
been as loyal as he.

07:37.991 --> 07:39.825
Especially after
the attack.

07:39.827 --> 07:41.827
CondÃ©.

07:41.829 --> 07:43.161
Yes, why not?

07:44.597 --> 07:45.464
Queen mary,

07:45.466 --> 07:46.631
We have
troubling word

07:46.633 --> 07:47.699
About one of your ladies.

07:51.804 --> 07:54.139
I've received an unsettling
report from the guards.

07:54.141 --> 07:56.475
A prisoner that
they are questioning

07:56.477 --> 07:59.244
Made a rather
outrageous claim.

07:59.246 --> 08:01.713
He says that your husband
is tied to the radicals

08:01.715 --> 08:03.081
Who attacked
the castle.

08:03.083 --> 08:05.484
That castleroy
funded them.

08:05.486 --> 08:07.986
What prisoner?

08:07.988 --> 08:09.588
I'm afraid it
doesn't matter.

08:09.590 --> 08:11.223
If there is any truth
to these claims,

08:11.225 --> 08:12.657
Any truth whatsoever,

08:12.659 --> 08:15.160
Francis and I may not
be able to save you.

08:15.162 --> 08:16.561
I know this is
terrible news,

08:16.563 --> 08:18.497
And I'm sorry to put
you through this.

08:18.499 --> 08:19.498
Put me through this?

08:19.500 --> 08:20.899
What exactly?

08:20.901 --> 08:23.535
Greer, you are one of
my oldest friends,

08:23.537 --> 08:25.570
And I love
and trust you,

08:25.572 --> 08:27.572
But I need to know if
there is any chance

08:27.574 --> 08:29.908
You could be linked to
this, however unjustly.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.910
If castleroy gave
money to protestants,

08:31.912 --> 08:34.579
If the radicals
were in your home,

08:34.581 --> 08:36.948
If there is any traceable
link to your household.

08:36.950 --> 08:38.950
No.

08:38.952 --> 08:40.519
No, of course not.

08:40.521 --> 08:43.054
My husband has always been
loyal, and, for me, I...

08:43.056 --> 08:44.789
I have never doubted
your loyalty.

08:48.628 --> 08:50.662
Leith: You're searching
your chambers to make sure

08:50.664 --> 08:51.897
There's nothing to tie you

08:51.899 --> 08:53.965
To castleroy's
treason, aren't you?

08:53.967 --> 08:55.567
Please don't deny it.

08:55.569 --> 08:56.868
I work with the guards.
I hear everything

08:56.870 --> 08:57.969
That comes out of the dungeons.

08:57.971 --> 08:59.137
It's not his treason, leith.

08:59.139 --> 09:00.272
It's ours.

09:01.607 --> 09:03.542
You knew castleroy
funded the attack?

09:03.544 --> 09:04.976
Neither one of us knew it.

09:04.978 --> 09:06.811
My husband thought
he was funding a school.

09:06.813 --> 09:08.313
We were tricked

09:08.315 --> 09:09.948
By the radicals.
Dear god.

09:09.950 --> 09:12.684
I almost confessed
to mary.

09:12.686 --> 09:14.619
Now I wish I had,
but I was so afraid.

09:15.788 --> 09:17.789
I can tell her the truth.

09:17.791 --> 09:19.324
I can throw myself on her mercy.

09:19.326 --> 09:21.192
No, mary's mercy
can't save you.

09:21.194 --> 09:23.228
Too many people were
killed in the attack.

09:23.230 --> 09:25.664
Too many nobles would
happily dangle your fate

09:25.666 --> 09:27.866
To extract a price
from francis and mary.

09:27.868 --> 09:29.334
And if they
can't pay it...

09:29.336 --> 09:31.970
Well, then what
can I do?
Think.

09:31.972 --> 09:34.005
If there's evidence anywhere,
we need to find it.

09:34.007 --> 09:35.140
I've been searching
through letters

09:35.142 --> 09:38.677
Well, is there anything else
written down? Anywhere?

09:38.679 --> 09:40.679
Think hard.

09:40.681 --> 09:42.814
I have wondered
about the counting house.

09:42.816 --> 09:44.583
He left it to me
as a source of income.

09:44.585 --> 09:47.586
It would hold
his personal ledger.

09:47.588 --> 09:51.222
If it lists any payments to men
now known as radicals...

09:51.224 --> 09:53.325
You'll die
for treason.

09:53.327 --> 09:55.727
Please help me, leith.

10:02.702 --> 10:06.037
Ah, why, diane.

10:06.039 --> 10:07.372
I heard you were back
to visit your son.

10:07.374 --> 10:10.208
How daring of you
to return.

10:10.210 --> 10:12.043
After you banished me?

10:12.045 --> 10:14.913
After you took away everything
that henry promised me?

10:14.915 --> 10:16.715
Come, now.

10:16.717 --> 10:18.717
You gained something
since henry's death.

10:18.719 --> 10:20.919
A daughter-in-law, kenna.

10:20.921 --> 10:24.689
Well, granted, she was henry's
discarded girlfriend.

10:24.691 --> 10:26.758
The one that replaced you.

10:27.760 --> 10:29.227
Ah, with a twitch of her ass.

10:29.229 --> 10:31.963
Enjoy your
expanded family.

10:31.965 --> 10:33.298
And what of your family?

10:33.300 --> 10:34.666
If claude's looks

10:34.668 --> 10:36.234
Could kill,
I do believe

10:36.236 --> 10:38.370
You'd be bathing
in your own blood.

10:43.409 --> 10:45.310
Princess claude.

10:45.312 --> 10:48.279
Ah, have you come
to steal a glance

10:48.281 --> 10:49.914
At your old mistress?

10:49.916 --> 10:52.083
Is it just me,

10:52.085 --> 10:54.753
Or does diane look a little
the worse for wear?

10:54.755 --> 10:56.121
Say it.

10:56.123 --> 10:57.756
I want to hear you say it.

10:57.758 --> 10:59.758
She looks old and too thin.

10:59.760 --> 11:02.127
So many mistakes,
I see them all

11:02.129 --> 11:03.895
So clearly now.

11:03.897 --> 11:07.332
That was a very
expensive mistake.

11:07.334 --> 11:10.735
What jealous tantrum
did that necklace pay for?

11:10.737 --> 11:12.404
(scoffs) look at claude.

11:12.406 --> 11:15.173
She's rubbing my nose in it.

11:15.175 --> 11:18.910
Making sure I see her kindness
to everyone else but me.

11:18.912 --> 11:21.846
I don't know why you subject
yourself to this torment,

11:21.848 --> 11:23.748
When you have another family
that loves you

11:23.750 --> 11:24.816
Without blame

11:24.818 --> 11:27.052
Or judgment.

11:29.689 --> 11:32.223
Because I wonder
about all this.

11:32.225 --> 11:35.326
Your new devotion to me.

11:35.328 --> 11:36.795
And these girls,

11:36.797 --> 11:38.697
Grown into the very image

11:38.699 --> 11:40.365
I had of them in my mind.

11:40.367 --> 11:43.101
Are you all in my mind?

11:43.103 --> 11:44.903
Or are you really here?

11:44.905 --> 11:47.038
Here to soothe my guilt

11:47.040 --> 11:48.807
For all the mistakes
that I made?

11:48.809 --> 11:49.908
What mistakes?

11:49.910 --> 11:52.343
I heard that bash

11:52.345 --> 11:55.113
Is helping claude find out
if she really killed the twins.

11:55.115 --> 11:58.083
Shouldn't I have been asking
those questions?

11:58.085 --> 11:59.784
If you had,

11:59.786 --> 12:00.952
You would've only
spread suspicion

12:00.954 --> 12:02.353
That claude was a monster.

12:02.355 --> 12:04.122
Instead,
you kept the evidence,

12:04.124 --> 12:06.257
Ample evidence,
to yourself.

12:06.259 --> 12:07.926
You even kept it from me.

12:08.961 --> 12:10.261
And I'm glad that you did.

12:10.263 --> 12:11.362
All you've ever done

12:11.364 --> 12:13.164
For your children is love

12:13.166 --> 12:16.735
Love in return is what
you deserve, catherine.

12:16.737 --> 12:17.502
Come.

12:17.504 --> 12:19.170
Let's get away from here, hm?

12:21.340 --> 12:23.408
Yes, let's.

12:25.845 --> 12:28.179
You said you thought
of something. What is it?

12:28.181 --> 12:30.849
Royal children are never alone.

12:30.851 --> 12:33.184
Yet I managed to sneak in
and stuff flowers

12:33.186 --> 12:34.886
Down the twins' throats?

12:34.888 --> 12:35.954
Where were their nannies
that night?

12:35.956 --> 12:37.889
I had the same question.

12:37.891 --> 12:39.791
I sought out all the nannies
that were here at that time.

12:39.793 --> 12:41.860
One of them died of old age.

12:41.862 --> 12:43.294
The others I'm having
a harder time finding.

12:43.296 --> 12:44.763
If you locate them,

12:44.765 --> 12:46.831
I want to question them
with you.

12:46.833 --> 12:48.767
Louis.

12:48.769 --> 12:50.301
If I'd known you were
staying at court

12:50.303 --> 12:52.370
To make winter supply deals,
I would never have sent

12:52.372 --> 12:53.805
My letter through
your envoy.

12:53.807 --> 12:56.474
Well, I just received it.

12:56.476 --> 12:58.409
I assume you're pleased.

12:58.411 --> 13:00.512
I might be if I could accept
these holdings.

13:00.514 --> 13:02.380
What do you mean? Why can't you?

13:02.382 --> 13:03.982
It doesn't feel right.

13:03.984 --> 13:05.550
Other protestant lords
have sacrificed more.

13:05.552 --> 13:06.951
They're more deserving.

13:06.953 --> 13:09.053
But francis, your king,
has made this offer.

13:09.055 --> 13:11.556
He's going to wonder
why you would refuse him.

13:11.558 --> 13:13.892
Let him wonder, then.
Perhaps he should.

13:14.894 --> 13:16.227
Louis, is this about

13:16.229 --> 13:18.263
The attack on the castle? On me?

13:18.265 --> 13:19.564
It's about all the attacks.

13:19.566 --> 13:21.499
Blood for blood for blood,
none of it needed

13:21.501 --> 13:23.835
If francis had simply said no
to a few catholic thugs.

13:23.837 --> 13:25.236
It's not that simple,
believe me.

13:25.238 --> 13:26.571
I know what the politics were.

13:26.573 --> 13:27.806
Please, I can't listen to you

13:27.808 --> 13:28.973
Defend the man any longer.

13:28.975 --> 13:30.141
Just once, I'd like

13:30.143 --> 13:31.342
To hear him defend himself.

13:31.344 --> 13:32.443
Louis.

13:32.445 --> 13:33.845
Please, listen.

13:33.847 --> 13:35.847
If you'll excuse me.

13:45.291 --> 13:47.458
I've never met a lady who
knew how to read accounts.

13:47.460 --> 13:50.295
My husband felt I should
understand his businesses.

13:50.297 --> 13:52.864
I'll review this
in its entirety this evening.

13:52.866 --> 13:54.866
I'd also like
my husband's personal ledger.

13:54.868 --> 13:56.434
He asked me to fetch it
for safekeeping.

13:56.436 --> 13:57.869
(chuckles)

13:57.871 --> 13:59.871
Safekeeping from whom,
the crown?

13:59.873 --> 14:01.606
I don't know what you mean.

14:01.608 --> 14:03.842
Surely you've heard the rumors
if I have.

14:03.844 --> 14:05.009
Word of financial ties

14:05.011 --> 14:06.878
Between your lord husband

14:06.880 --> 14:08.079
And radical protestants.

14:08.081 --> 14:10.882
I can assure you
that no such ties exist.

14:10.884 --> 14:12.350
But if they did,

14:12.352 --> 14:14.252
The evidence would be
in his personal ledger.

14:14.254 --> 14:15.587
That's why I've taken

14:15.589 --> 14:17.522
The precaution of hiding it.

14:17.524 --> 14:19.924
The lady has asked
for her property.

14:19.926 --> 14:22.060
I think it'd be best
you deliver it.

14:22.062 --> 14:24.128
The lady and I are partners.

14:24.130 --> 14:25.530
It benefits neither of us

14:25.532 --> 14:26.865
For the book to be found.

14:26.867 --> 14:28.266
The crown confiscates

14:28.268 --> 14:30.468
Any business belonging
to traitors.

14:30.470 --> 14:32.270
You have me at a disadvantage.

14:32.272 --> 14:34.138
You know where the ledger is;
I do not.

14:34.140 --> 14:37.275
You're too good at business
not to expect some price.

14:37.277 --> 14:39.944
Your husband deeded me
51% of this business

14:39.946 --> 14:42.013
So it would be legally held
by a man.

14:42.015 --> 14:44.515
I should like my ownership
to be complete.

14:50.456 --> 14:51.623
Don't do it, greer.

14:51.625 --> 14:53.892
What choice do I have?

14:56.395 --> 14:59.097
Remember, if that book is found,

14:59.099 --> 15:01.165
I'll make sure the crown knows
you were my partner

15:01.167 --> 15:03.001
In its concealment as well.

15:03.003 --> 15:04.502
They might take your head,

15:04.504 --> 15:07.505
As well as your new
counting house.

15:07.507 --> 15:11.009
Bash: It took me longer
to find the twins' nanny.

15:11.011 --> 15:12.510
She changed her name
after marrying.

15:12.512 --> 15:14.245
She did more than marry.

15:14.247 --> 15:16.915
She married a noble.

15:16.917 --> 15:18.950
Wonder how she managed that.

15:20.920 --> 15:23.154
I hope I haven't kept you.

15:23.156 --> 15:26.057
It's a great honor being invited
to speak with your highness.

15:26.059 --> 15:27.258
If this is about
your charity project,

15:27.260 --> 15:29.427
My husband and I would
be honored to...

15:29.429 --> 15:30.695
Actually, we were hoping
to speak with you

15:30.697 --> 15:32.497
About your time at the castle.

15:32.499 --> 15:33.932
When you were a nanny.

15:33.934 --> 15:35.533
Oh.

15:35.535 --> 15:37.702
Lady yvonne,
I hope our questions

15:37.704 --> 15:39.003
Aren't making you uncomfortable.

15:39.005 --> 15:40.538
You seem...

15:40.540 --> 15:42.240
As if you might crawl
out of your skin.

15:42.242 --> 15:44.609
Do press on, bash.

15:44.611 --> 15:48.179
I'm upset because those
were such sad days.

15:48.181 --> 15:51.049
When the twins died,
we were all very distraught.

15:51.051 --> 15:52.350
You say you were there
when the bodies were found.

15:52.352 --> 15:54.686
Can you tell us exactly
what happened?

15:54.688 --> 15:58.056
I'd only gone out for a moment
or two to use the privy,

15:58.058 --> 15:59.090
And when I came back,

15:59.092 --> 16:00.725
They were dead.

16:00.727 --> 16:03.027
Both of them?

16:03.029 --> 16:04.729
Didn't you think that was odd?

16:04.731 --> 16:06.097
Were you there
when the doctor came?

16:06.099 --> 16:07.465
Did you see him

16:07.467 --> 16:08.633
Pull the flowers
from their throats?

16:08.635 --> 16:10.034
Yes, of course.

16:10.036 --> 16:11.202
Bash, it was her.

16:11.204 --> 16:12.737
I don't know what you mean.

16:12.739 --> 16:14.138
There were only three people

16:14.140 --> 16:15.273
Who knew
about the flowers, yvonne.

16:16.208 --> 16:17.342
The doctor who found them,

16:17.344 --> 16:19.010
Catherine, who alone was told,

16:19.012 --> 16:20.478
And the person
who put them there.

16:20.480 --> 16:22.080
You killed them.

16:22.082 --> 16:23.214
How could you do
such a thing? Why?

16:23.216 --> 16:25.083
I didn't, I swear.

16:25.085 --> 16:26.985
The babies were dead
when I found them.

16:26.987 --> 16:28.219
What are you talking about?

16:28.221 --> 16:30.054
And be very clear,
or you will hang,

16:30.056 --> 16:31.723
And I will cheer for your death.

16:31.725 --> 16:33.624
He was the king.

16:33.626 --> 16:37.428
How was I supposed to say no?

16:38.630 --> 16:40.365
<i>He was relentless.</i>

16:40.367 --> 16:42.400
<i>He'd come into the nursery.</i>

16:42.402 --> 16:45.303
<i>He'd follow me</i>
<i>to my chambers at night.</i>

16:45.305 --> 16:47.372
Then, one night,
he pulled me into a corner.

16:47.374 --> 16:51.042
<i>He wanted me to try some kind</i>
<i>of new turkish smoke.</i>

16:51.044 --> 16:52.643
<i>It was a simpler request</i>

16:52.645 --> 16:55.013
<i>Than his others.</i>

16:55.015 --> 16:57.215
After that,
I lost track of time.

16:57.217 --> 16:59.017
<i>Of myself.</i>

16:59.019 --> 17:00.718
<i>When I woke,</i>
<i>I ran back to the nursery,</i>

17:00.720 --> 17:03.454
<i>But hours and hours</i>
<i>had gone by,</i>

17:03.456 --> 17:05.556
<i>And I found the windows</i>
<i>blown open by the wind.</i>

17:05.558 --> 17:07.558
<i>It was freezing in there.</i>

17:07.560 --> 17:09.260
I must have forgotten
to latch them.

17:09.262 --> 17:11.095
<i>I ran to the babies,</i>

17:11.097 --> 17:12.764
<i>But they'd stopped breathing.</i>

17:12.766 --> 17:15.733
<i>I tried to warm them,</i>
<i>but it was no use.</i>

17:15.735 --> 17:17.769
And then I realized
what would happen to me

17:17.771 --> 17:19.470
If the queen found out.

17:19.472 --> 17:22.140
<i>I saw claude's little dress</i>
<i>in the corner--</i>

17:22.142 --> 17:24.342
<i>The one with the flowers</i>
<i>torn off--</i>

17:24.344 --> 17:26.144
And I knew the answer.

17:26.146 --> 17:28.179
So after my sisters
froze to death,

17:28.181 --> 17:30.615
You shoved flowers
into their mouths

17:30.617 --> 17:32.417
And waited for my mother
to blame me?

17:32.419 --> 17:34.585
I hoped she would think
you were too young

17:34.587 --> 17:36.354
To know what you'd done.

17:36.356 --> 17:38.056
I hoped she'd forgive you.

17:38.058 --> 17:40.158
She did not forgive me.

17:40.160 --> 17:41.292
Why weren't
you punished

17:41.294 --> 17:42.427
For leaving your post?

17:42.429 --> 17:43.828
Don't you see?

17:43.830 --> 17:46.064
Mother and father both
covered up for her

17:46.066 --> 17:47.632
Without realizing the
other was doing it.

17:47.634 --> 17:49.267
Mother didn't want
any questions asked,

17:49.269 --> 17:50.635
Because she told
that fever story

17:50.637 --> 17:52.103
So no one thought
me a monster.

17:52.105 --> 17:54.205
And father married you
off to some noble

17:54.207 --> 17:56.074
To make sure
you never told mother

17:56.076 --> 17:57.508
Where you really were that
night, isn't that right?

17:57.510 --> 17:59.544
Please, forgive me.

17:59.546 --> 18:01.345
I was afraid of your parents.

18:01.347 --> 18:03.214
Both of them.
Well, now you
can be afraid of me!

18:03.216 --> 18:04.415
You killed my sisters

18:04.417 --> 18:06.150
And made me pay for it

18:06.152 --> 18:07.452
My entire life!

18:07.454 --> 18:09.253
Claude, there will be justice,
I promise you.

18:09.255 --> 18:10.421
Guards, please take

18:10.423 --> 18:12.223
This woman away.
No!

18:12.225 --> 18:13.224
Oh, no, please!

18:13.226 --> 18:14.592
Please, your highness.

18:14.594 --> 18:16.194
Forget about her.

18:16.196 --> 18:18.262
What matters is
you're innocent.

18:18.264 --> 18:19.797
You've always been innocent.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.866
(sighs)

18:21.868 --> 18:24.168
God.

18:24.170 --> 18:26.137
Come on, mother!

18:26.139 --> 18:28.106
Coming.

18:28.108 --> 18:29.607
Forget the ice festival;
come with us!

18:29.609 --> 18:31.375
I need rest.

18:31.377 --> 18:32.877
Are you having
as much fun as I am?

18:32.879 --> 18:35.880
I am, as-as much as I can.

18:35.882 --> 18:37.348
As much as you can?

18:39.585 --> 18:42.720
I want to enjoy myself, I do,

18:42.722 --> 18:43.754
But how can I

18:43.756 --> 18:45.790
When you bring me such pleasure,

18:45.792 --> 18:48.226
But also such pain?

18:48.228 --> 18:51.562
I hid the truth
about your murders,

18:51.564 --> 18:56.200
But if claude killed you,
I raised a monster.

18:56.202 --> 18:58.903
And if she didn't, I have been
treating her like one

18:58.905 --> 19:00.271
For no reason.

19:00.273 --> 19:02.340
So long ago, catherine.

19:02.342 --> 19:03.875
Who could blame you?

19:03.877 --> 19:05.710
You lost your babies.

19:05.712 --> 19:07.378
Don't second-guess yourself,

19:07.380 --> 19:09.347
Or you will go mad.

19:09.349 --> 19:11.182
(girls giggling)

19:11.184 --> 19:12.850
What about claude?

19:12.852 --> 19:14.285
Shouldn't I be with her now?

19:14.287 --> 19:15.286
You think she needs you?

19:15.288 --> 19:16.921
That francis needs you?

19:16.923 --> 19:18.823
Not anymore.

19:18.825 --> 19:20.758
The girls need you.

19:20.760 --> 19:22.860
They have no one but us,

19:22.862 --> 19:25.830
And unlike your other children,
they're asking for you.

19:25.832 --> 19:29.200
Catherine, be the mother
they want.

19:29.202 --> 19:31.836
Be the mother they need.

19:31.838 --> 19:35.773
