from the front line â™ª

19:35.775 --> 19:38.242
â™ª it's been here

19:38.244 --> 19:39.443
(laughter)

19:39.445 --> 19:43.681
â™ª the whole time

19:43.683 --> 19:48.719
â™ª I sleep to keep my mind
at ease â™ª

19:48.721 --> 19:52.456
â™ª I wander through a dream

19:52.458 --> 19:56.827
â™ª of what I once believed

20:05.437 --> 20:07.705
â™ª my love

20:07.707 --> 20:11.809
â™ª the drums are calling

20:11.811 --> 20:15.713
â™ª a red sky

20:15.715 --> 20:18.816
â™ª a warning.

20:27.259 --> 20:29.327
(grunting)

20:36.435 --> 20:39.503
I understand you've had
some issues with my rule.

20:39.505 --> 20:41.439
You refuse my offers

20:41.441 --> 20:44.742
You-you don't like the way
I handle dissent?

20:44.744 --> 20:47.545
I've questioned a few
of your acts of repression, yes.

20:47.547 --> 20:50.381
Do you know where I hear
about most of your dissent?

20:50.383 --> 20:51.449
Mary tells you.

20:51.451 --> 20:53.317
My ambassadors tell me,

20:53.319 --> 20:54.619
My lords tell me,
everyone at court

20:54.621 --> 20:56.487
Tells me, except for my wife,

20:56.489 --> 20:57.788
Who says barely a word.

20:57.790 --> 20:59.457
You think mary's
still protecting me?

20:59.459 --> 21:01.392
I think it's lucky for you
that she does.

21:01.394 --> 21:04.462
I think it's sad that either of
us should need her protection.

21:05.497 --> 21:06.998
And that one of us
utterly failed

21:07.000 --> 21:08.899
To protect her
just when she needed it most.

21:11.803 --> 21:14.572
I warn you, cousin.

21:14.574 --> 21:16.574
Your words are unwise.

21:18.277 --> 21:20.378
Perhaps we should
leave our words aside.

21:20.380 --> 21:21.812
Air our differences
sportingly.

21:21.814 --> 21:23.481
You've played quarterstaff, yes?

21:28.520 --> 21:30.655
I should go back inside.

21:30.657 --> 21:32.356
It's so cold.

21:32.358 --> 21:33.391
Girls, enough
fun for now.

21:33.393 --> 21:35.493
Run back inside.

21:36.662 --> 21:39.530
Your mother and I
will be along shortly.

21:39.532 --> 21:42.066
Oh, my god, catherine...

21:42.068 --> 21:45.069
To see all this light again.

21:45.071 --> 21:47.571
It was so dark without you.

21:47.573 --> 21:49.540
And you...

21:49.542 --> 21:51.509
So beautiful.

22:03.755 --> 22:05.656
Henry, stop.

22:05.658 --> 22:08.025
I'm shivering.
And I'm offering warmth.

22:08.027 --> 22:09.627
More than warmth.

22:10.829 --> 22:13.464
Heat.
Oh.

22:13.466 --> 22:14.532
Do you feel it?

22:14.534 --> 22:16.834
Hmm?
Yes.

22:16.836 --> 22:18.436
Oh, keep doing that.

22:18.438 --> 22:21.472
(laughs)

22:21.474 --> 22:22.707
Trust me, I know what you need.

22:22.709 --> 22:24.608
What is that?

22:24.610 --> 22:26.544
Me.

22:27.512 --> 22:29.580
Us.

22:29.582 --> 22:31.082
Together forever.

22:32.451 --> 22:34.885
What did you used to say to me?

22:36.521 --> 22:39.557
When we'd make love
and I was so near...

22:43.962 --> 22:46.630
You're almost home.

22:54.506 --> 22:56.040
(exhales)

22:57.743 --> 22:59.877
(grunting)

23:07.652 --> 23:09.687
Is there something between
them we don't know about?

23:14.893 --> 23:17.661
(grunting)

23:17.663 --> 23:18.963
(spectators gasp)

23:24.536 --> 23:26.670
You're what's
between them.

23:29.908 --> 23:31.175
(grunting)

23:41.853 --> 23:43.587
Enough! Stop!

24:00.138 --> 24:02.773
Bash:
Catherine?

24:02.775 --> 24:04.542
Catherine!

24:05.777 --> 24:07.111
Henry.

24:08.113 --> 24:09.780
What on earth are you doing?

24:09.782 --> 24:12.116
You'll freeze to death.

24:12.118 --> 24:14.218
You're lucky I found you.

24:14.220 --> 24:16.220
I was looking for you.

24:16.222 --> 24:17.955
A servant saw you
by the garden door.

24:17.957 --> 24:20.124
I followed your
footprints.

24:20.126 --> 24:21.859
Why are you helping me?

24:21.861 --> 24:24.695
That's a very
good question.

24:24.697 --> 24:27.064
So henry lured the nanny away

24:27.066 --> 24:29.633
And the twins froze to death,
poor things.

24:30.802 --> 24:32.169
And then she framed claude

24:32.171 --> 24:33.838
To try to cover her neglect.

24:33.840 --> 24:36.040
Where is she now?
In the dungeon.

24:36.042 --> 24:38.576
She'll be punished,

24:38.578 --> 24:40.244
But who will punish me?

24:40.246 --> 24:42.012
You thought you were
protecting your daughter.

24:42.014 --> 24:43.981
Yes, I believed that.

24:43.983 --> 24:46.183
I think I was just trying
to protect myself

24:46.185 --> 24:48.185
By not asking questions

24:48.187 --> 24:50.654
I didn't want to know
the answers to.

24:51.656 --> 24:53.991
Was my daughter truly guilty?

24:53.993 --> 24:56.193
What damage did our
terrible marriage

24:56.195 --> 24:58.896
Do to our children?

25:00.732 --> 25:03.801
I knew they were hurt.

25:03.803 --> 25:07.071
I didn't know
it cost them their lives.

25:08.974 --> 25:12.276
Oh, he hurt your mother, too.

25:12.278 --> 25:14.545
I think she knew what
she was getting into.

25:14.547 --> 25:17.548
Oh, you're wrong about that.

25:17.550 --> 25:19.116
Once we had enough heirs,

25:19.118 --> 25:21.652
Henry convinced diane
that he'd be all hers.

25:21.654 --> 25:23.554
How do you know this?

25:23.556 --> 25:24.989
Because he told me

25:24.991 --> 25:27.558
There would be no more
carnal relations between us.

25:27.560 --> 25:30.528
He was going to try to be
faithful to his mistress.

25:30.530 --> 25:31.829
Of course, he never was.

25:31.831 --> 25:33.264
I know that

25:33.266 --> 25:34.932
Because of all the
things he bought her,

25:34.934 --> 25:36.934
Just to quell
her rage.

25:36.936 --> 25:39.303
It was quite a temper
your mother had,

25:39.305 --> 25:40.938
When she found out
he'd betrayed her.

25:40.940 --> 25:43.574
Oh, but
the gifts:

25:43.576 --> 25:44.942
Chateaus, jewels,

25:44.944 --> 25:47.244
That ridiculous chapel
he had built

25:47.246 --> 25:49.313
With all that stained glass.

25:49.315 --> 25:51.248
That was after the
twins were born.

25:51.250 --> 25:54.151
Carnal relations never
ended with us, either.

25:54.153 --> 25:56.954
What? What is it?

25:56.956 --> 25:58.789
It's nothing.

25:58.791 --> 26:00.824
I hope it brings you some peace

26:00.826 --> 26:03.060
To know your daughter
didn't kill the twins.

26:03.062 --> 26:04.895
I should go.

26:04.897 --> 26:06.230
Such haste.

26:06.232 --> 26:07.898
I haven't properly mocked you

26:07.900 --> 26:10.100
For saving the life
of your mother's worst enemy.

26:12.604 --> 26:15.105
(door closes)

26:16.241 --> 26:18.309
I shouldn't have
let him provoke me.

26:18.311 --> 26:21.078
But, mary, he did provoke me.

26:21.080 --> 26:24.782
There is something in condÃ©
that needs to be dealt with.

26:24.784 --> 26:26.083
His anger towards me

26:26.085 --> 26:27.751
Is not just about

26:27.753 --> 26:30.054
My mistakes as a ruler.

26:30.056 --> 26:31.989
He has feelings for you,

26:31.991 --> 26:34.959
And now everyone knows it.

26:38.263 --> 26:42.066
And you think that
I encouraged him?

26:42.068 --> 26:43.801
Francis, have you not
been hearing

26:43.803 --> 26:45.336
A word I've said?

26:45.338 --> 26:47.638
I can barely
stand to touch

26:47.640 --> 26:48.739
My own husband.

26:48.741 --> 26:51.141
Why would I...
Ever encourage another?

26:51.143 --> 26:54.178
I know you don't think
you will heal,

26:54.180 --> 26:56.947
But I know
that you will.

26:56.949 --> 26:58.649
You are a survivor

26:58.651 --> 27:00.317
And the strongest person
I've ever known.

27:00.319 --> 27:02.119
It may be too soon

27:02.121 --> 27:04.888
To talk about this,

27:04.890 --> 27:07.358
And it is excruciating

27:07.360 --> 27:09.760
To have to say this to you,
given what you've been through,

27:09.762 --> 27:11.729
But, mary,

27:11.731 --> 27:14.665
This notion of
"separate lives..."

27:14.667 --> 27:16.333
Living separate lives

27:16.335 --> 27:18.202
Is not a solution;
it is a threat.

27:18.204 --> 27:20.304
And not just to our marriage,
but to our rule.

27:20.306 --> 27:22.239
When you give us

27:22.241 --> 27:23.741
An heir someday,

27:23.743 --> 27:26.276
As I have every faith
that you will,

27:26.278 --> 27:28.879
There cannot be
the slightest doubt

27:28.881 --> 27:31.382
About our child's paternity.

27:31.384 --> 27:34.218
Doubts like these start wars.

27:34.220 --> 27:36.186
They put your
country at risk,

27:36.188 --> 27:37.688
As well as your life.

27:37.690 --> 27:39.423
My life.

27:39.425 --> 27:41.058
And not yours.

27:41.060 --> 27:43.193
I know. It is unfair.

27:43.195 --> 27:44.928
My mother was almost beheaded

27:44.930 --> 27:46.797
For infidelity,
while my father

27:46.799 --> 27:48.399
Had every woman
that he wanted.

27:48.401 --> 27:50.668
But that is the way that it is,

27:50.670 --> 27:51.902
Right or wrong.

27:51.904 --> 27:53.437
I remind you
of this

27:53.439 --> 27:54.772
Because I care for you.

27:54.774 --> 27:58.208
Oh, was that "caring"?

27:58.210 --> 28:00.144
It sounds to me like a man

28:00.146 --> 28:02.146
Trying to tighten
his grip on a woman.

28:02.148 --> 28:04.281
You'll understand

28:04.283 --> 28:07.251
If I don't stay to hear more.

28:16.728 --> 28:19.296
Oh, thank you, elise.

28:19.298 --> 28:20.431
There you are,
my queen.

28:20.433 --> 28:22.132
I'm sorry
for letting

28:22.134 --> 28:23.967
Our fun outside get out of hand.

28:23.969 --> 28:26.203
I'd forgotten what cold
can do to the living.

28:26.205 --> 28:28.005
You've forgotten a lot
of things, haven't you?

28:28.007 --> 28:31.041
Like the nanny
that let the twins die

28:31.043 --> 28:33.944
Because she was too busy
with you in bed.

28:35.146 --> 28:36.447
I beg your pardon.

28:37.882 --> 28:40.184
Maybe you honestly
don't remember.

28:40.186 --> 28:41.752
Maybe that's
not your fault,

28:41.754 --> 28:43.454
As I invited you here,
such as you are.

28:43.456 --> 28:44.888
Such as I am?

28:44.890 --> 28:45.889
What am I?

28:45.891 --> 28:47.991
You're a lie, henry.

28:47.993 --> 28:51.161
Because I brought you here
to ease my conscience.

28:51.163 --> 28:53.497
Oh, but you were a lie
in life, too.

28:53.499 --> 28:57.234
Everything you ever spoke of
or promised were all lies.

28:57.236 --> 28:59.269
Loyalty, duty...

28:59.271 --> 29:00.738
Even France.

29:00.740 --> 29:02.372
Nothing mattered more to you
than yourself.

29:02.374 --> 29:04.775
Why are you
arguing, mother?

29:04.777 --> 29:07.277
Because, my darlings,
I'm afraid

29:07.279 --> 29:10.147
Our time together
must come to an end.

29:10.149 --> 29:12.916
Now, you need
to find peace,

29:12.918 --> 29:14.418
Away from this place.

29:14.420 --> 29:17.087
I will be with you
one day, I promise.

29:17.089 --> 29:20.023
To you, it will seem very soon.

29:22.861 --> 29:24.161
Good-bye,

29:24.163 --> 29:25.462
My loves.

29:25.464 --> 29:28.031
Good-bye, mother.
Good-bye, mother.

29:36.307 --> 29:37.508
Oh...

29:37.510 --> 29:39.042
Oh, they're gone.

29:39.044 --> 29:40.310
Catherine...
It was that simple.

29:40.312 --> 29:41.545
Don't break up our family.

29:41.547 --> 29:44.014
Don't you dare speak of family.

29:44.016 --> 29:46.016
You have no idea
what that word means.

29:46.018 --> 29:47.484
A family is more
than one person.

29:47.486 --> 29:48.952
A family is loving people,

29:48.954 --> 29:51.522
Thinking of others
before themselves.

29:51.524 --> 29:55.192
I have always loved
you and the children.

29:55.194 --> 29:56.560
When it was convenient.

29:56.562 --> 29:57.995
When it didn't keep you

29:57.997 --> 29:59.797
From your indulgences
that you crave.

30:00.865 --> 30:02.499
I took you back into my bed

30:02.501 --> 30:04.802
Again and again,
because I loved you.

30:04.804 --> 30:06.470
I taught you

30:06.472 --> 30:08.472
That it was all right
to treat your family

30:08.474 --> 30:10.407
With scorn and neglect.

30:10.409 --> 30:13.544
And look how our children
suffered because of it.

30:13.546 --> 30:15.979
The twins are gone.

30:15.981 --> 30:17.881
I may have lost claude forever.

30:17.883 --> 30:19.983
I will never forgive myself
for that.

30:19.985 --> 30:21.251
Or you.

30:21.253 --> 30:23.520
I will always bear

30:23.522 --> 30:26.890
My guilt,
but I will not bear you.

30:26.892 --> 30:28.826
I want you out
of my life, henry.

30:28.828 --> 30:29.860
Do you hear me?

30:29.862 --> 30:32.329
I don't want you back!

30:32.331 --> 30:34.031
I don't want
you at all.

30:34.033 --> 30:35.833
You're nothing to me.

30:35.835 --> 30:37.167
You're dead.

30:37.169 --> 30:38.836
You're nothing
but dust and bile.

30:38.838 --> 30:39.870
It isn't that easy, catherine.

30:39.872 --> 30:41.104
Oh, begone,

30:41.106 --> 30:42.940
Ghost of my past,

30:42.942 --> 30:45.576
My mistakes,
my foolishness.

30:45.578 --> 30:47.578
Return to your hell

30:47.580 --> 30:49.580
And leave me to mine!

30:59.591 --> 31:01.592
Bash.

31:01.594 --> 31:02.960
What's wrong?

31:02.962 --> 31:04.962
When I was young,
you always told me

31:04.964 --> 31:07.197
That we were
father's real family.

31:07.199 --> 31:08.899
That catherine and her children

31:08.901 --> 31:10.500
Were just for show,
for politics.

31:10.502 --> 31:11.935
You said I shouldn't

31:11.937 --> 31:13.437
Be jealous of them,
and I wasn't.

31:13.439 --> 31:16.440
I loved my brothers and sisters.

31:16.442 --> 31:18.008
But what about you?

31:18.010 --> 31:19.443
Were you threatened by them

31:19.445 --> 31:21.612
In some way?
What are you on about, darling?

31:21.614 --> 31:24.281
Catherine mentioned the chapel
that father built for you.

31:24.283 --> 31:25.515
Do you remember it?

31:25.517 --> 31:27.918
With all that expensive
stained glass?

31:27.920 --> 31:30.187
Because I remember
a day in that chapel.

31:30.189 --> 31:32.122
Damn you, henry!

31:32.124 --> 31:33.924
Damn you!

31:33.926 --> 31:36.493
(screams)

31:36.495 --> 31:39.596
Father told me that that chapel
<i>wasn't built only for you,</i>

31:39.598 --> 31:41.331
But also for me.

31:41.333 --> 31:44.067
After it was unveiled,
he snuck me inside,

31:44.069 --> 31:47.004
And we etched our initials
in the lead, he and I,

31:47.006 --> 31:50.007
Along with the date.

31:50.009 --> 31:52.609
That's why I saved
this piece here, you see?

31:52.611 --> 31:55.679
'cause it was right after this
that you wrecked the window.

31:55.681 --> 31:57.080
I checked the book
of records, mother,

31:57.082 --> 31:58.949
And two days later,
the twins were dead.

31:58.951 --> 32:01.385
You were cursing at father
when you broke this glass.

32:01.387 --> 32:03.387
Were you still angry

32:03.389 --> 32:06.924
That he'd slept with catherine
to conceive the twins?

32:06.926 --> 32:09.493
Or was it about him
seducing the nanny?

32:09.495 --> 32:13.397
Or was it all part of the same
betrayal, eating you up inside?

32:14.933 --> 32:18.068
Do you think it was easy
being the king's mistress?

32:18.070 --> 32:19.469
Hmm?

32:19.471 --> 32:21.271
A position
easily gained.

32:21.273 --> 32:23.273
But held?

32:23.275 --> 32:25.275
For decades?

32:25.277 --> 32:27.644
Say it was an accident,
mother, please.

32:27.646 --> 32:30.347
Say that you only left
those nursery windows open

32:30.349 --> 32:33.583
To get the nanny dismissed,
to keep your hold on the king.

32:33.585 --> 32:35.585
I would like to say that.

32:35.587 --> 32:37.154
I would.

32:37.156 --> 32:39.990
I wanted catherine
to suffer.

32:39.992 --> 32:41.725
I wanted henry
to suffer.

32:41.727 --> 32:43.961
They did.

32:43.963 --> 32:46.697
The estate I offered
is no longer yours.

32:47.966 --> 32:49.299
I will protect your secret

32:49.301 --> 32:50.634
If you leave today.

32:50.636 --> 32:52.636
But I can't bear to look
at you as you are now,

32:52.638 --> 32:53.971
Much less hanging
from a rope.

32:53.973 --> 32:55.973
Go and never come back.

32:55.975 --> 32:57.341
I am your mother.

32:57.343 --> 32:59.176
Where is your forgiveness?

32:59.178 --> 33:00.677
You absolved your wife,

33:00.679 --> 33:02.179
Even though she was
your father's mistress.

33:02.181 --> 33:05.248
How can you even compare
kenna's affair to this?

33:05.250 --> 33:06.650
She was young
and naive.

33:06.652 --> 33:08.085
She was scared.

33:08.087 --> 33:09.419
You killed
two baby girls.

33:09.421 --> 33:11.121
Kenna, young
and naive?

33:11.123 --> 33:13.123
That doesn't describe
the girl who told catherine

33:13.125 --> 33:15.492
I was in rome
trying to get you legitimized.

33:16.661 --> 33:18.662
What are you talking about?

33:18.664 --> 33:20.130
Kenna would never do that.

33:20.132 --> 33:21.198
But she did.

33:21.200 --> 33:23.066
Ask catherine.

33:23.068 --> 33:26.136
Kenna knew that exposing my plan
could get us both killed,

33:26.138 --> 33:27.571
But she wanted
me gone.

33:27.573 --> 33:30.073
Determined to strike
at her rival for henry.

33:30.075 --> 33:33.143
Just as I was when I left
that nursery window open.

33:33.145 --> 33:36.713
If that's true, then neither
of you deserves my forgiveness.

33:36.715 --> 33:38.782
This is good-bye.

33:40.585 --> 33:41.785
We will never see
one another again.

33:41.787 --> 33:43.754
Bash.

33:51.429 --> 33:53.430
Is francis all right?

33:53.432 --> 33:55.499
Francis is fine.

33:56.601 --> 33:58.602
Lola, I have a favor
to ask of you.

33:58.604 --> 34:00.604
You won't like it,

34:00.606 --> 34:03.673
But if you are loyal to me,
you won't question it.

34:05.810 --> 34:08.712
Mary asked you to offer yourself
as a possible match for me?

34:08.714 --> 34:11.748
Not as directly
as that, but yes.

34:11.750 --> 34:14.084
What does she take us for?
A couple of game pieces

34:14.086 --> 34:15.819
She can shunt aside
to unclutter her board?

34:15.821 --> 34:18.755
Actually, she said she hoped
we'd admire each other

34:18.757 --> 34:20.757
As much as she
admires us.

34:20.759 --> 34:24.394
So we might find the happiness
she's found with francis.

34:28.066 --> 34:29.800
All very neat
and tidy, isn't it?

34:29.802 --> 34:31.268
Well, hardly.

34:32.437 --> 34:34.071
Perhaps you think you're some

34:34.073 --> 34:36.273
Gallant defender of mary's,
but look around.

34:36.275 --> 34:39.342
You've spawned harmful gossip
with your male pride,

34:39.344 --> 34:41.278
And she's doing everything
she can to stop it.

34:41.280 --> 34:44.114
I don't care if your heart
leads you my way or not,

34:44.116 --> 34:45.849
But I won't have it
lead you to mary.

34:45.851 --> 34:47.284
She's my oldest friend,

34:47.286 --> 34:49.352
And I'll see her protected
from any threat,

34:49.354 --> 34:51.254
Gallant or otherwise.

34:51.256 --> 34:53.590
You're quite fierce
when you want to be, aren't you?

34:53.592 --> 34:54.858
Are you mocking me?

34:54.860 --> 34:57.194
I'm admiring you.

34:58.863 --> 35:00.630
All right, then.

35:00.632 --> 35:03.166
Shall we take our royal orders
and see where they lead us?

35:12.610 --> 35:14.144
Your majesty.

35:14.146 --> 35:15.712
You asked for evidence

35:15.714 --> 35:17.380
Proving the castleroy's
innocence.

35:18.716 --> 35:21.451
This is castleroy's
personal ledger,

35:21.453 --> 35:23.854
Found in his counting house.

35:23.856 --> 35:28.258
Its contents will confirm guilt
rather than innocence.

35:42.340 --> 35:44.241
Mary?

35:45.843 --> 35:48.145
I don't know how
much time I have,

35:48.147 --> 35:49.880
But before
this is done,

35:49.882 --> 35:52.883
There are things I
need you to know.

35:52.885 --> 35:54.718
I lied to you, mary,

35:54.720 --> 35:57.254
And that is a
treason in itself.

35:57.256 --> 36:00.157
But aloisius did
nothing wrong...

36:00.159 --> 36:02.192
Greer, stop.

36:02.194 --> 36:04.728
The ledger we found
in your counting house is enough

36:04.730 --> 36:07.564
To prove your guilt in the eyes
of the catholic nobles.

36:09.400 --> 36:11.501
It is not quite enough
in the eyes of the king.

36:11.503 --> 36:13.937
No one can prove

36:13.939 --> 36:16.173
Which protestants you thought
you were giving your money to.

36:16.175 --> 36:17.507
Then I'll live.

36:17.509 --> 36:18.909
Francis and I have
made sure of that, yes.

36:18.911 --> 36:20.744
In the deal we made
with the nobles,

36:20.746 --> 36:23.847
You may keep your life,
but that is all you may keep.

36:23.849 --> 36:27.417
You will lose your title,
your lands, your holdings,

36:27.419 --> 36:28.952
Your rooms
here at the castle

36:28.954 --> 36:31.188
And your position with me.

36:31.190 --> 36:33.823
But where will I live?

36:33.825 --> 36:34.925
H-how will I live?

36:34.927 --> 36:37.761
That can no longer be
my concern.

36:37.763 --> 36:39.429
Or lola's.
Or kenna's.

36:39.431 --> 36:40.864
I'm sorry.

36:40.866 --> 36:42.866
Because I'm a traitor now.

36:42.868 --> 36:44.334
A pariah.

36:44.336 --> 36:46.503
(knocking on door)
one more moment, please.

36:46.505 --> 36:48.205
One more moment--
is that all we have?

36:53.878 --> 36:55.946
The wagon is ready
to take her away.

36:55.948 --> 36:58.281
Nobles are waiting.

36:59.317 --> 37:00.984
Promise me you'll take care.

37:00.986 --> 37:03.820
Promise me, greer,
for it is a dangerous world.

37:03.822 --> 37:04.955
I will.

37:04.957 --> 37:07.457
Thank you.

37:07.459 --> 37:08.858
Good-bye.

37:20.605 --> 37:23.607
I'm so tired of waiting
for liars to tell me the truth.

37:23.609 --> 37:25.242
It's exhausting,
you know that?

37:25.244 --> 37:26.243
Did you hear about greer?

37:26.245 --> 37:27.410
It's so awful.

37:27.412 --> 37:28.878
This time,
I don't want to wait.

37:28.880 --> 37:32.415
You should tell me the truth
without being asked.

37:32.417 --> 37:34.618
Did you tell catherine that
my mother was talking to rome

37:34.620 --> 37:35.685
About getting me legitimized?

37:37.021 --> 37:38.788
I could have been
executed, kenna.

37:38.790 --> 37:39.923
I wasn't thinking
about that.

37:39.925 --> 37:41.324
(groans in frustration)

37:41.326 --> 37:43.293
I just wanted your
mother out of the way.

37:43.295 --> 37:44.794
I was scared.

37:44.796 --> 37:46.029
I couldn't go
back to scotland,

37:46.031 --> 37:47.797
And I couldn't find
a husband here.

37:47.799 --> 37:49.432
I thought I might
lose everything.

37:49.434 --> 37:51.301
And which did you fear
losing the most?

37:51.303 --> 37:53.436
The gifts and privileges
of sharing a bed with the king?

37:53.438 --> 37:54.838
Or his love?

37:54.840 --> 37:56.006
Both.

37:56.008 --> 37:58.275
Is that what you
want to hear?

37:58.277 --> 38:00.343
Is that what I should have said
when we married?

38:00.345 --> 38:02.646
That, yes, I loved him.

38:02.648 --> 38:04.414
Before he went mad.

38:04.416 --> 38:06.283
You never told me that.

38:06.285 --> 38:07.517
Why would I?

38:07.519 --> 38:09.819
You asked me to give us
a chance, so I did.

38:11.656 --> 38:13.923
Bash, you have no idea what it's
like to be a girl in this world.

38:13.925 --> 38:16.026
Owning nothing,
having no power

38:16.028 --> 38:18.395
Except the effect
that you have on men.

38:19.497 --> 38:20.930
The king noticed me,

38:20.932 --> 38:23.033
And for the first
time, I mattered.

38:23.035 --> 38:24.834
What was I
supposed to do?

38:24.836 --> 38:26.503
Throw it away?

38:26.505 --> 38:28.705
Did you throw away mary's
love when you had it?

38:28.707 --> 38:31.441
Besides, why are we even
fighting about this?

38:31.443 --> 38:33.076
Everybody makes mistakes.

38:33.078 --> 38:34.778
It's in the past.

38:34.780 --> 38:36.713
Some things can't stay
in the past.

38:36.715 --> 38:38.715
Some things are
too unforgivable.

38:38.717 --> 38:41.718
When a person is willing
to sacrifice lives

38:41.720 --> 38:43.720
For their own petty interests--

38:43.722 --> 38:46.022
That is one of those things.

38:54.398 --> 38:55.865
Francis:
Mary?

38:55.867 --> 38:58.601
I hate to disturb you, but...

38:58.603 --> 38:59.869
Are you all right?

38:59.871 --> 39:01.938
After everything
that happened with greer.

39:01.940 --> 39:03.373
The truth?

39:04.508 --> 39:07.644
No, I'm not all right.

39:07.646 --> 39:11.047
I've been thinking about all
that we've been through,

39:11.049 --> 39:13.116
My ladies and I.

39:13.118 --> 39:14.617
And sometimes I wonder

39:14.619 --> 39:16.019
If I should have even
brought them with me.

39:16.021 --> 39:19.456
I would have felt
very alone if I hadn't.

39:19.458 --> 39:21.124
As I do now.

39:23.627 --> 39:26.463
Your words were hard to hear,
but they were true.

39:26.465 --> 39:29.499
Appearances matter
for people like us.

39:29.501 --> 39:32.902
CondÃ© and I can appear
to have no friendship

39:32.904 --> 39:34.704
That is more than political.

39:34.706 --> 39:37.040
I can't stand to see you hurt.

39:38.376 --> 39:40.577
I don't want you
to feel so alone.

39:40.579 --> 39:42.579
But I am alone.

39:42.581 --> 39:43.813
We both are.

39:43.815 --> 39:44.981
We don't have to be.

39:46.584 --> 39:49.119
I'd like to stay
with you tonight.

39:50.421 --> 39:53.056
Not for appearances
or politics

39:53.058 --> 39:56.493
Or because you are my wife.

39:56.495 --> 40:00.029
Just to watch over you
while you sleep.

40:00.031 --> 40:01.664
I could stay here.

40:01.666 --> 40:04.100
Happily.

40:09.607 --> 40:11.674
I would like that.

40:20.518 --> 40:21.785
My god...

40:21.787 --> 40:23.787
Catherine.

40:23.789 --> 40:27.624
I admit I was slow
to put it together,

40:27.626 --> 40:30.960
Much to my poor daughter
claude's misfortune.

40:30.962 --> 40:34.197
Then I heard-- bash has
taken away your estate,

40:34.199 --> 40:35.899
Told you to leave.

40:35.901 --> 40:37.434
I started thinking.

40:37.436 --> 40:39.436
The nanny may believe
that the wind

40:39.438 --> 40:42.439
Blew open the
nursery windows.

40:42.441 --> 40:44.207
That isn't possible.

40:44.209 --> 40:45.809
They have
latches on them.

40:45.811 --> 40:48.812
Human hands had to open them.

40:48.814 --> 40:50.814
Jealous hands.

40:50.816 --> 40:53.983
It never occurred to me
that a mother would do this

40:53.985 --> 40:56.186
To another mother's child.

40:57.721 --> 40:59.989
Don't you want to beg
for your life?

40:59.991 --> 41:02.225
You're a hypocrite.

41:02.227 --> 41:04.727
How many mother's children
have you killed?

41:04.729 --> 41:08.164
Oh, indignation
instead of groveling?

41:08.166 --> 41:10.633
